{"id": "EUVD-2022-55292", "enisaUuid": "6f93358e-22fd-3106-88bb-50a56003c566", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nASoC: SOF: Intel: hda-ipc: Do not process IPC reply before firmware boot\n\nIt is not yet clear, but it is possible to create a firmware so broken\nthat it will send a reply message before a FW_READY message (it is not\nyet clear if FW_READY will arrive later).\nSince the reply_data is allocated only after the FW_READY message, this\nwill lead to a NULL pointer dereference if not filtered out.\n\nThe issue was reported with IPC4 firmware but the same condition is present\nfor IPC3.", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T12:30:42", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-14T18:31:26", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/48945246cf802b9866f3a821103f1a7a196baf68", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/499cc881b09c8283ab5e75b0d6d21cb427722161", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50015"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50015"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "90130528-3e36-3787-9596-f3a3b7d498f1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19.4"}, {"id": "a103e227-22c4-31a4-bbff-c6aa0c0e35c2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6e9cde974863dc9d9c6cdb178f625e410c5be3d0 <48945246cf802b9866f3a821103f1a7a196baf68"}, {"id": "b7c215e1-822d-3fc1-8cd3-99a46ac32012", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0"}, {"id": "dd63635e-05db-3c0a-be77-afb10a05f1ae", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6e9cde974863dc9d9c6cdb178f625e410c5be3d0 <499cc881b09c8283ab5e75b0d6d21cb427722161"}, {"id": "f19e7210-fcda-36a7-8a63-9ca8741c86fd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "f78744e9-8ce5-3515-a99e-3a37fc3d4d35", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.2"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "cd94d665-9484-3c6e-b37e-3aec0a379db5", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}